    • onSaveBtnClick

      void onSaveBtnClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException, SQLException
      This method is called if the Save button is selected. The TextFields are parsed, a new Customer object is created and added to the Inventory ObservableList as well as the mySQL database. The window is then returned to the apptCustomer.fxml file.
      Parameters:
      event - The event of the Save button being clicked
      Throws:
      IOException
      SQLException

    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL location, ResourceBundle resources)
      This method is called when the addCustomer.fxml file is loaded. The ID text field is disabled and populated with a random value. The Country ComboBox is populated with existing data from Inventory.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      location - The location of the relative path of the root object.
      resources - Resource used to localize the root object; can be null if absolute path.
